{
  "name": "TaskFlow Complete Automation",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "httpMethod": "POST",
        "path": "taskflow-issues",
        "responseMode": "responseNode",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "webhook-issues",
      "name": "Webhook - Issues",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.webhook",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        250,
        300
      ],
      "webhookId": "taskflow-issues-webhook-id"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "string": [
            {
              "value1": "={{$json.body.event}}",
              "value2": "issue.created"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "id": "if-issue-created",
      "name": "If Issue Created",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        470,
        300
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "string": [
            {
              "value1": "={{$json.body.issue.priority}}",
              "value2": "high"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "id": "if-high-priority",
      "name": "If High Priority",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        690,
        200
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "functionCode": "// Auto-Assignment Logic\n// Maps issue type to the responsible team member\n// Bug → Nandhini (backend dev)\n// Feature / Story → Frontend developer\n// Epic / Task → Project Lead\n\nconst item = items[0].json;\nconst issue = item.body.issue;\nconst type = (issue.type || 'task').toLowerCase();\n\nconst assignmentMap = {\n  'bug':     'Nandhini',\n  'task':    'Nandhini',\n  'story':   'Nandhini',\n  'feature': 'Nandhini',\n  'epic':    'Nandhini',\n  'subtask': 'Nandhini',\n};\n\nconst assigneeName = assignmentMap[type] || 'Nandhini';\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    ...item,\n    autoAssign: {\n      assigneeName,\n      issueId: issue.id,\n      issueKey: issue.key,\n      issueTitle: issue.title,\n      issueType: type,\n      priority: issue.priority,\n    }\n  }\n}];"
      },
      "id": "auto-assign-logic",
      "name": "Auto-Assign Logic",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.function",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        910,
        200
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "url": "=http://localhost:5001/api/issues/{{$json.autoAssign.issueId}}/assign",
        "authentication": "genericCredentialType",
        "genericAuthType": "httpHeaderAuth",
        "sendHeaders": true,
        "headerParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            {
              "name": "x-n8n-secret",
              "value": "n8n-taskflow-secret-2024"
            },
            {
              "name": "Content-Type",
              "value": "application/json"
            }
          ]
        },
        "sendBody": true,
        "bodyParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            {
              "name": "assignee",
              "value": "={{$json.autoAssign.assigneeName}}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {
          "response": {
            "response": {
              "neverError": true
            }
          }
        }
      },
      "id": "update-issue-assign",
      "name": "Update Issue Assignment",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.1,
      "position": [
        1130,
        200
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ✅ Auto-Assignment Complete\n\n**Issue:** {{$json.autoAssign.issueKey}} — {{$json.autoAssign.issueTitle}}\n**Type:** {{$json.autoAssign.issueType}}\n**Priority:** 🔴 {{$json.autoAssign.priority}}\n**Auto-Assigned To:** {{$json.autoAssign.assigneeName}}\n\n*Notification sent to assignee via TaskFlow in-app system.*"
      },
      "id": "format-assignment-summary",
      "name": "Format Assignment Summary",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.markdown",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1350,
        200
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ⏭️ Skipped — Not High Priority\n\n**Issue:** {{$json.body.issue.key}} — {{$json.body.issue.title}}\n**Priority:** {{$json.body.issue.priority}}\n\n*Automation only triggers for HIGH priority issues.*"
      },
      "id": "skip-not-high",
      "name": "Skip - Not High Priority",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.markdown",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        910,
        380
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "respondWith": "json",
        "responseBody": "={\"received\": true, \"event\": \"{{$json.body.event}}\", \"status\": \"processed\"}"
      },
      "id": "respond-webhook",
      "name": "Respond to Webhook",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.respondToWebhook",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        690,
        380
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "httpMethod": "POST",
        "path": "taskflow-sprints",
        "responseMode": "lastNode",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "webhook-sprints",
      "name": "Webhook - Sprints",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.webhook",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        250,
